                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14464197" author="ven" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2008 08:00:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would also be happy to know if this is legal code, if the variable should be seen inside the loop body.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14464213" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2008 08:05:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I recall, assignments is forbidden in if() but not in while().&lt;br/&gt;
But at any rate, the VerifyError is a bug!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477823" author="paulk" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2008 16:33:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At the moment, a logical expression or an assignment is legal but a declaration is illegal in a while. I have a patch which puts out an error message, i.e. gets rid of the VerifyError. I also worked on a patch to add declaration support. It is a little tricky in that you need to get scoping correct. Would our goal be to emulate Java? Or do we just not support it for now?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477875" author="paulk" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2008 06:25:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, added a compilation error message for now (just in HEAD at the moment). We can remove that error message if we provide full support. I guess the error message is good enough for 1.5.2 and we could target 1.6 for re-introducing proper support.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14464243" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 31 Jan 2008 09:56:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;there was an error in the grammar that allowed declarations for while, synchronized and switch. I disabled this now&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
